class reference could help, so let’s dig deeper into this!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class reflection issues**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether to ensure the BCDHPrivateKey class is included for `Class.forName` with a static final field. I've noted that native `Class.forName` fails for classes not registered for reflection. It seems that this only works for classes known at build time, and ObjectInputStream class names from streams need reflection metadata. The coverage report about \\\"dynamic-access call sites\\\" suggests those calls must be executed under native conditions. I’m considering whether the original test didn’t use the concrete BCDHPrivateKey type for serialization.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering type adjustments**\\n\\nI'm thinking about changing the serialize and deserialize types to the concrete `BCDHPrivateKey`. It seems like using a dynamic agent could help generate conditional metadata when the concrete type is reached. By using the concrete type as a parameter, return type, and locally, I might improve the native serialization metadata and coverage tracking. However, I'm still facing a `ClassNotFound` issue with `ObjectInputStream`, even though the class literal appears in the cast and import. I need to address that.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating JVM test outcomes**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the JVM test passes after the last run and if agent metadata is generated. There’s a ClassNotFound issue that arose earlier, which showed up after the 20:00 timestamp. I’m trying to understand if the native code ran after the agent but didn’t produce any metadata. It’s possible that the agent is only generating metadata for user code in default mode. There’s a bit of uncertainty here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9FXd7ekhJlJn2HUkaXL7doBd|fc_0510b239bb690582016a25b22e744c819082514eeafee29cb1", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/build -type f \\( -name 'reflect-config.json' -o -name 'serialization-config.json' -o -name 'reachability-metadata.json' \\) -print | sort | xargs -r -n1 sh -c 'echo --- $0; head -80 \"$0\"'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2249, "output": 2182, "cacheRead": 41984, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46415, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780855288185, "responseId": "resp_0510b239bb690582016a25b1f8d3688190a9d1fe234d184937"}}
